Potential impact? This could significantly advance single-image depth completion in sparse-LiDAR scenarios (e.g., urban driving), or enhance few-shot 3D reconstruction where texture cues are minimal (e.g., medical imaging or industrial inspection). Moreover, the framework generalizes beyond RGB-D inputs—it could be adapted to event cameras or polarimetric data where auxiliary signals hint at geometry.

